# Installation & Usage
Option 1: Run using the Heroku link above.

Option 2: Run on command line.
List of Scripts
```json
    "scripts": {
    "start": "node server/server.js",
    "develop": "concurrently \"cd server && npm run watch\" \"cd client && npm start\"",
    "install": "cd server && npm i && cd ../client && npm i",
    "build": "cd client && npm run build"
```

These are the steps to run MERN-BookWorm from the command line in develop mode 
1. Set up the environment by installing node package manager on the server and client side

	* npm install
	 invokes build script:
	  "install": "cd server && npm i && cd ../client && npm i",
 
2. Start client and server code
	* npm run develop
	
	This will concurrently start both client and server
	Successful output is:

	webpack 5.88.1 compiled successfully in 3575 ms
	Now listening on port: 3000

3. Open localhost:3000

4. Follow the prompts to signup/login and explore books

5. Open Chrome Development Tools (right click "Inspect" on browser)

